New-Melting Script Notes: Runs new-melting.cpp several times to generate data and plots data

Edit script file:  /home/kirstie/deft/papers/fuzzy-fmt/figs/Kir_scripts/kir_new-melting_script.sh
Run script file from Kir_scripts directory as:   ./kir_new-melting_script.sh

The script file runs /home/kirstie/deft/papers/fuzzy-fmt/figs/new-melting.cpp several times generating data and creating the data file:  newmeltdataout.dat in Kir_scripts directory

The script file then runs /home/kirstie/deft/papers/fuzzy-fmt/figs/Kir_scripts/newmeltdataout.cpp 
which uses newmeltdataout.dat to create plot file: newmeltdataout.gnu in Kir_scripts directory

The script file runs gnuplot with pause command to show the plot. Alternatively, to see the plot start gnuplot (enter "gnuplot") and type load 'newmeltdataout.gnu' to display the plot.

FILES to commit:

   kir_new-melting_script.sh
   new-melting.cpp
   newmeltdataout.cpp


*Remember to compile newmeltdataout.cpp using g++ newmeltdataout.cpp -o newmeltdataout
*Remember to make script file executable using chmod u+x kir_new-melting_script.sh




